  "text": "We consider only homogeneous patterns of SSEs from the top-ranked configuration [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] , and we define two SSEs to be in contact if the distance between the midpoints of their associated vectors is less than a given threshold (18Å in our analysis). Notice that, following our definition, in a motif not all pairs of SSEs must be in contact; it is enough that every SSE is in contact with at least another SSE. In our case of four SSEs, a motif should have at least three pairs of SSEs in contact. Figure 6 shows the number of SSEs in contact for the quartets of segments with the top angular pattern.",
